==== Suez ====
  +
The city of Suez has seen the most violence of the protests thus far. Eyewitness reports have suggested that the death toll there may be higher, although confirmation has been difficult due to a ban on media coverage in the area.<ref name="rawstory.com">{{cite web|last=Tencer |first=Daniel |url=http://www.rawstory.com/rs/2011/01/reports-massacre-suez-protests-egypt/ |title=Reports of âmassacreâ in Suez as protests in Egypt move into third day |publisher=Raw Story |date=14 January 2011 |accessdate=28 January 2011}}</ref> Some online activists have referred to Suez as Egypt's [[Sidi Bouzid]], the Tunisian city where protests started.<ref>{{cite news|last=Dziadosz|first=Alexander|title=Could Suez be Egypt's Sidi Bouzid?|url=http://af.reuters.com/article/egyptNews/idAFLDE70Q1KZ20110127|accessdate=29 January 2011|work=[[Reuters]]|date=27 January 2011}}</ref>
